<div id="review_4136284338" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4136284338" />
    <a title="Noorie Hassan" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/120721498-noorie-hassan"><img alt="Noorie Hassan" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1598937728p2/120721498.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4136284338?book_show_action=true">Jul 28, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Noorie Hassan" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Noorie Hassan" href="/user/show/120721498-noorie-hassan">Noorie Hassan</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4136284338" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2491464447649229819">Thank you J. R. Weaver for sending me a copy of The Addiction Manifesto. This is a self-help book and it not only tells a story but also conveys important messages and lessons. The book is based on a true story of an army veteran; the addiction tale of the author himself, who bravely fought this ill and stepped out of it. The author tells how he was blinded by drugs and how addiction deprived him of his family, friends and even life. Addiction is tricky and always succeeds in tearing away the no</span>
  <span id="freeText2491464447649229819" style="display:none">Thank you J. R. Weaver for sending me a copy of The Addiction Manifesto. This is a self-help book and it not only tells a story but also conveys important messages and lessons. The book is based on a true story of an army veteran; the addiction tale of the author himself, who bravely fought this ill and stepped out of it. The author tells how he was blinded by drugs and how addiction deprived him of his family, friends and even life. Addiction is tricky and always succeeds in tearing away the normal lives of people. The author describes addiction as a serious disease and it doesn’t care about colour, religion, race or gender; it just wraps itself around you and fogs your vision to see the reality, to see the real world. Don’t let your ego invade your consciousness, because battling addiction makes you a warrior. A hospital/rehabilitation institute helped the author to recover and eventually positive results manifested. This book is a detailed guide for recovery with straightforward language that can be understood easily. It consists of some interesting facts and figures, quotes, cycles, principles and recovery stories of other addicts. The author did great with writing down his experience and making it helpful for others. This book will give you motivation, teach you to believe in yourself and give yourself a chance for a better life because recovery isn’t for those who need it, rather for those who want it. Thumbs up!</span>
  <a data-text-id="2491464447649229819" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


