        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4350693950" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2186188564980231063">I don’t even know where to start, this book was eye-opening. I am not in any means an addict, to anything (other than books! :)) However, I know the journey is long and very difficult with many obstacles. <br/><br/>I think it is admirable that JR Weaver has written about his journey, documented it for himself and others to see that although it seems impossible to change your life around… if you are persistent and determined, you will be able to do it. <br/><br/>I loved the personal touches of quotes from JR Weaver,</span>
  <span id="freeText2186188564980231063" style="display:none">I don’t even know where to start, this book was eye-opening. I am not in any means an addict, to anything (other than books! :)) However, I know the journey is long and very difficult with many obstacles. <br /><br />I think it is admirable that JR Weaver has written about his journey, documented it for himself and others to see that although it seems impossible to change your life around… if you are persistent and determined, you will be able to do it. <br /><br />I loved the personal touches of quotes from JR Weaver, pictures and the Recovery Stories from others who have fought hard to get where they are today. <br /><br />I thought this was a great read, I read it in one sitting. It had me tearing up in places due to the stories told, JR Weavers fight. <br /><br />I am so grateful to have been an opportunity to be on this book tour arranged by the lovely @zooloosbooktour. Thank you to jrweaver0 for allowing me a copy of this gem. <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="2186188564980231063" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
